
# ** Format
# <type>(<optional scope>): <emoji> <subject>
# [BLANK LINE]
# <optional body>
# [BLANK LINE]
# <optional footer>
#
# ** Type
# * 👷 build:    changes affecting build process or auxiliary tools
# * 🤖 chore:    changes that don't modify src or test files
# * 💚 ci:       ci/cd related changes
# * 📝 docs:     documentation only changes
# * ✨ feat:     a new feature
# * 🐛 fix:      a bug fix
# * ⚡️ perf:     a code change that improves performance
# * ♻️  refactor: a code change that neither fixes a bug or adds a feature
# * 🚀 release:  create a release commit
# * ⏪ revert:   revert previous changes
# * 🎨 style:    changes that do not affect the meaning of the code (white­space, formatting, missing semi-colons, etc)
# * ✅ test:     adding missing or correcting existing tests
#
# ** Subject
# * use the imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# * no dot (.) at the end.
#
# ** Scope
# * provide additional contextual information
# * contained within parenthesis
#
# ** Body
# * use the imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
# * should include the motivation for the change and contrast this with
#   previous behavior
#
# ** Footer
# * reference any tasks/tickets/issues related to this commit
# * breaking changes start with "BREAKING CHANGE:", or appends "!" after the
#   type/scope
#
# ** Additional Notes:
# * subject line 50 chars
# * body/footer 72 chars
